    {
      "id": "IrQHSpJGA1qm9iEGqPF7W",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 268,
      "y": 403,
      "width": 1063.0791015625,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 681720995,
      "version": 264,
      "versionNonce": 1807324461,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773896545703,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- This can be used in asynchronous call from producer to consumer.\n- Retry capability is added if a message fails\n- PACE matching - when a multiple client send message to queue, consumer can consume them in same pace.\n ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 93,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- This can be used in asynchronous call from producer to consumer.\n- Retry capability is added if a message fails\n- PACE matching - when a multiple client send message to queue, consumer can consume them in same pace.\n ",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "oNK2VDdy-3uib9ojv0SoX",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 289,
      "y": 514,
      "width": 1168.3790283203125,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 297078637,
      "version": 578,
      "versionNonce": 834664717,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773897483643,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Different messaging type \n1) Point to point -> Publisher publishes message and we have consumer and message will be consumed by one consumer.\n2) Pub/sub -> When publisher publishes based on the exchange logic it broadcasts message to all the queue. So same\nmessage can be consumed by multiple consumer.\n\nWorking of messaging queue :\n1) KAFKA : \nIt has components like Producer, consumer, consumer group, topic, partition, offset, cluster, zookeeper.\nIn distributed system mutiple brokers, so zookeeper helps to communication between each broker.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 218,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Different messaging type \n1) Point to point -> Publisher publishes message and we have consumer and message will be consumed by one consumer.\n2) Pub/sub -> When publisher publishes based on the exchange logic it broadcasts message to all the queue. So same\nmessage can be consumed by multiple consumer.\n\nWorking of messaging queue :\n1) KAFKA : \nIt has components like Producer, consumer, consumer group, topic, partition, offset, cluster, zookeeper.\nIn distributed system mutiple brokers, so zookeeper helps to communication between each broker.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
